  <section><div class="wrap">
    <div class="pillar"><h3>Defense innovation</h3><p>I analyze how technology and organization combine to create advantage in defense and security — and what those dynamics reveal about innovation in civilian markets.</p></div>
    <div class="pillar"><h3>AI</h3><p>AI already delivers insight, decision support, and autonomy. The challenge is no longer whether the capability exists, but whether organizations can use it: successful adoption is an organizational problem, not a model problem.</p></div>
    <div class="pillar"><h3>Cybersecurity capacity building</h3><p>National strategies, sectoral resilience, and institutional capability designed to endure — not another one-off report.</p></div>
  </div></section>
  <section><div class="wrap">
    <p class="eyebrow">First principles</p>
    <p class="lead">The doctorate isn't decoration. It's the discipline to reason from first principles when the playbooks don't fit — to see the whole system, separate signal from noise, and, as Michael Porter put it, decide what not to do. Where the ground shifts and the stakes are national, that rigor is the difference between motion and progress.</p>
  </div></section>
